records.addlTxt:
Count 1, NO CONTEST plea to the amended charge of delivery of THC.  Convicted.
Count 2 is dismissed and read in on State's motion.
Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.  Conditions of probation:
1) Nine (9) months Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law.  Five (5) months to be served up front, commencing 11-01-16 by 5:00 p.m.  Four (4) months stayed, to be imposed at agent's discretion;
2) AODA assessment and follow through (If the assessment defendant has already completed is ok with the agent, the Court strikes this condition) ;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Random drug screens, and pays for same;
5) Maintain full-time employment, school or combination;
6) COMPAS assessment;
7) Provide a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
8) Pay costs of the action; and
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Court does not feel expungement is appropriate in this case.  Court does not grant expungement.
Defendant is to be given 1 day jail credit.
Minutes.
